Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel, and cut @yellow onion{1}(halved and peeled) into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince one or two wedges until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise); cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons.

On a #baking sheet{}, toss carrots and onion wedges with a drizzle of @oil{1%tbsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until lightly browned, ~{10%minutes}.

Once veggies have roasted 10 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully add zucchini and a pinch of salt; toss to combine.

Return to top rack and roast until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes} more.

While veggies roast, peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb} until you have ½ tsp (1 tsp for 4 servings). Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce}(trimmed and sliced) (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!).

== Turkey Patties ==

In a #large bowl{}, combine @ground turkey{10%ounce}, minced onion, minced ginger, @salt{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), and pepper. Mix gently until thoroughly combined. Form into 6 1 1/2-inch meatballs (12 meatballs for 4).

> TIP: Rub hands with a little oil first to prevent sticking.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add meatballs; gently press down with a #spatula{} to form ½-inch-thick patties. Cook until browned and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} per side (for 4, you may need to work in batches).

Turn off heat; transfer patties to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan and let cool for ~{1%minute}.

== Mushroom Teriyaki ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium heat. Add mushrooms and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and slightly crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}.

While mushrooms cook, whisk together @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, @gochujang sauce{1/2%ounce}, half the @cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, and @water{1/2%cup} (all the cornstarch and 1 cup water for 4 servings) in a #small bowl{}.

Once mushrooms are done, add soy-gochujang mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add cooked turkey patties and @butter{1/2%tablespoon} (1 TBSP for 4); turn patties to evenly coat. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

== To Serve ==

Divide veggie jumble and glazed turkey patties between plates in separate sections.

Spoon any remaining sauce over patties and sprinkle with as many @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} as you like. Serve.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.